         Firstly, there are ways to break guilds other than a prime time frontal assault on their city. We have been tearing guilds apart since before there were cities to knock down, since before the so called “first generation MMORPG’s” existed (which by the way, we consider second generation). We’ve been in the business of bleeding fools like you for over 10 years now. It’s the sheep like you that make it possible, to kill a guild one would prey on the weak and the stupid.  <P>Secondly, you are nothing more than a lemming. In those 10 years we have existed we have seen countless sheep just like you with the exact same song and dance. You apply to KAAOS, get ignored first...laughed at when you continue to query...pissed on when, in lieu of crawling back under your insignificant rock, you start preaching about how KAAOS will be squashed by newb guild 20000045 in x game. It used to be funny but after the 10 billion fucks who looked just like you, smelled just like you, squealed just like you, who came before you, it just becomes old and tired. <P>We don’t deal in the weak, we don’t deal in the stupid. If there is one weak link the chain breaks. We devour our recruits because if they can’t take the punishment by their “family” how the fuck can we trust them to take the heat against our enemies? No weak links. Each KAAOSer can smell fear and weakness a mile away. If they smell it coming from another KAAOSer you bet your ass they will be there, like a pirana, to take little pieces out of them. If they draw blood the rest of the pack is attracted and a feeding frenzy begins and, believe me, once that happens there is nothing left behind. The feeding frenzy is even more fierce when it’s a KAAOSer who’s exposed their soft white underbelly than it is for our enemies. <P>A quote from the mouth of babes:<BR><i>“Trying to have this "orginized sport" while using name calling might make it hard to have quality players and players that will stay. “</i><P>We are all about quality, something a guild that invites someone to join with no prior knowledge of their ability, of their character, of their intelligence can possibly compete with. For some people it can take years to be recognized as KAAOS. We have never had a KAAOSer outright quit the guild, not in 10 years. We’ve had some retire, we’ve booted a few, but KAAOS is definitely not a revolving door. <P>The bottom line is, one cannot “become” KAAOS. You were either born KAAOS or you weren’t. And you.....are not KAAOS. <P>Azmodion<BR>Lord of Misery<BR>KAAOS God of Misfortune
